===subject:Chapter 5 Reply
===from:Carla Foster
===date:Tue Mar  4 17:33:49 2003
===message:I think the shining moment of reconstruction went beyond people willing to fight for black suffrage and civil rights.  Although short lived, it was a reality.  Freedman were able to vote and even served in southern legislatures for the first time in American history.  There was, however, a striking difference between the black officeholders and the freedman who voted for them.  Officeholders cared about obtaining equal rights and what was most important to freedman was their economic future - land acquisition.
=========yorg=========
