===message:I also agree with you.  Reconstruction could have been successful if they had the backing of the military to ensure that the rights of blacks were not being infringed upon.  The radical republicans were thought to be radical because they believed blacks should be treated equally and that blacks should be enfranchised.  Unfortunately people started to turn their backs on black suffrage.  The government was more concerned with the unification of the states than of the rights of blacks.
